WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:03:26.433 --> 00:03:29.200
Helsinki. one hour. Senator.

3
00:03:30.471 --> 00:03:33.741
- Is POTUS up and about yet?
- POTUS status unknown. sir.

4
00:03:33.841 --> 00:03:36.778
Actually. I heard him moving around
just now. I think he's awake. sir.

5
00:03:37.778 --> 00:03:39.777
Enter.

6
00:03:41.541 --> 00:03:43.351
Morris. Good morning.

7
00:03:43.451 --> 00:03:45.683
Mr. President. sir.

8
00:03:48.255 --> 00:03:52.293
Well. here we go again.
Twenty points down in the polls.

9
00:03:52.393 --> 00:03:56.828
Friends and enemies lining up
to stab me in the back.

10
00:03:57.398 --> 00:04:00.166
Well. at least you're still
in my corner. Right. Morris?

11
00:04:05.706 --> 00:04:08.042
Come on. you're not gonna tell
the first lady. are you?

12
00:04:08.142 --> 00:04:11.145
Wheels down in Helsinki in an hour. sir.

13
00:04:11.724 --> 00:04:16.248
I'd rather take a bullet than go through
another one of these conferences.

14
00:04:18.085 --> 00:04:19.987
That was insensitive.

15
00:04:20.087 --> 00:04:23.791
Saying something like that to a man
who actually took a bullet for me.

16
00:04:23.891 --> 00:04:27.929
Well. a near-death experience does change
one's prospective on a few things. sir.

17
00:04:28.029 --> 00:04:32.266
Look. Morris. I'm really sorry
I'm forcing you to retire after this trip.

18
00:04:32.366 --> 00:04:34.524
I know how you feel.

19
00:04:37.505 --> 00:04:41.352
Mr. President. sir. one thing
I have learned is that...

20
00:04:42.009 --> 00:04:46.745
life is just too damn short not to have
a cookie when you want one.

21
00:04:47.715 --> 00:04:50.081
See you in a half?

22
00:06:16.671 --> 00:06:19.139
<i>Welcome to Lapland. gentlemen.</i>

23
00:06:19.239 --> 00:06:21.045
A real hunting paradise.

24
00:06:21.145 --> 00:06:24.045
We've got moose. We've got bears.

25
00:06:24.145 --> 00:06:28.749
We've got wolves. lynx.
Everything in here.

26
00:06:28.849 --> 00:06:32.617
So... what kind of game
are you looking for?

27
00:06:33.154 --> 00:06:35.423
- Big game.
- <i>Roger. sir.</i>

28
00:06:35.523 --> 00:06:38.711
<i>You're gonna get it. I promise.</i>

29
00:06:39.421 --> 00:06:42.497
Great. Land the helicopter.

30
00:06:42.797 --> 00:06:45.566
We haven't the license
to hunt here on this area.

31
00:06:45.866 --> 00:06:48.169
Just execute my order.

32
00:06:48.269 --> 00:06:50.301
Roger. sir.

33
00:06:50.671 --> 00:06:52.398
Goddamn.

34
00:07:42.089 --> 00:07:45.259
Never seen a hunting team like this.

35
00:07:45.359 --> 00:07:47.391
I expect not.

36
00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:53.665
What you got there?
Something like scope?

37
00:07:54.902 --> 00:07:57.104
It's a targeting system.

38
00:07:57.204 --> 00:07:59.974
Targeting system? What for?

39
00:08:00.074 --> 00:08:01.075
Right.

40
00:08:01.175 --> 00:08:03.744
Shoulder-mounted. Chinese
FN-6 surface-to-air missile.

41
00:08:03.844 --> 00:08:06.664
Not the most advanced SAM
on the market by any means. but...

42
00:08:06.764 --> 00:08:09.851
more than capable of taking out
passenger aircraft.

43
00:08:09.951 --> 00:08:11.886
Passenger aircraft? What do you mean?

44
00:08:12.186 --> 00:08:15.411
A civilian aircraft. I should say.

45
00:08:15.923 --> 00:08:19.108
With a state-of-the-art military grade
aircraft. the defense systems

46
00:08:19.208 --> 00:08:21.962
would most likely deflect the attack.

47
00:08:22.062 --> 00:08:24.932
Unless. that is...

48
00:08:25.032 --> 00:08:27.899
The defense systems
had somehow been disabled.

49
00:08:30.838 --> 00:08:32.540
Are you...

50
00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:36.244
Are you terrorists?

51
00:08:37.244 --> 00:08:41.245
You certainly look terrified.
so I suppose we must be.

52
00:08:43.885 --> 00:08:47.151
But I don't think you should be
worrying about us.

53
00:08:47.822 --> 00:08:50.906
You should be worrying about yourself.

54
00:08:51.006 --> 00:08:53.163
In fact. in my opinion.
you should be running.

55
00:08:54.128 --> 00:08:56.263
- Running?
- Absolutely.

56
00:08:56.363 --> 00:08:59.701
You see. I intend to kill you.
You have no way of overpowering me.

57
00:08:59.801 --> 00:09:04.169
but I don't yet have a weapon in my hand.
so your best chance is to run.

58
00:09:06.073 --> 00:09:07.772
Like this.

59
00:10:10.637 --> 00:10:14.709
<i>ABC of Hunting.
Volume Four. for Beginners.</i>

60
00:10:15.109 --> 00:10:18.012
<i>Attracting deer to within
your shooting range.</i>

61
00:10:18.112 --> 00:10:19.947
<i>This might be
a little difficult at first.</i>

62
00:15:07.267 --> 00:15:10.204
- Sir.
- John.

63
00:15:10.304 --> 00:15:11.738
What's our ETA?

64
00:15:11.838 --> 00:15:14.899
Forty-five miles.
We just started our descent.

65
00:15:14.999 --> 00:15:17.744
Excellent. I'll tell POTUS.

66
00:15:17.844 --> 00:15:19.746
And try not to rock the boat
on the way down.

67
00:15:19.846 --> 00:15:21.730
You know how he hates
to spill his coffee.

68
00:15:21.830 --> 00:15:23.715
Okay.

69
00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:36.296
- Oh. shit! Joe. you got this?
- Affirmative.

70
00:15:36.396 --> 00:15:38.599
- What's going on?
- Someone is targeting us with a SAM.

71
00:15:38.699 --> 00:15:41.868
Holy shit! F-18 escort is reporting
the same. They're lit up too.

72
00:15:41.968 --> 00:15:44.302
- Joe. engage countermeasures now.
- The counters won't engage.

73
00:15:44.402 --> 00:15:47.317
- What?
- Something is jamming us. It's like...

74
00:15:47.417 --> 00:15:49.397
- I've lost power.
- Jesus Christ!

75
00:15:49.497 --> 00:15:52.112
All stations. initiate emergency
evacuation procedure.

76
00:15:52.212 --> 00:15:54.689
The President is under attack.
I repeat...

77
00:15:54.789 --> 00:15:58.481
Emergency evacuation.
The President is under attack.

78
00:16:01.188 --> 00:16:03.157
What the hell is going on?

79
00:16:03.257 --> 00:16:04.591
We've got to get you
out of here. Mr. President.

80
00:16:04.691 --> 00:16:06.727
- What about my shoe?
- Forget your damn shoe!

81
00:16:07.829 --> 00:16:09.034
Go. go. go!

82
00:16:16.736 --> 00:16:18.272
Otis. what's going on?

83
00:16:18.372 --> 00:16:21.415
You're getting off this plane.
Mr. President.

84
00:16:24.578 --> 00:16:26.747
I'll take it from here.
Get the man on the ground.

85
00:16:26.847 --> 00:16:29.049
- Roger that.
- Are we under attack?

86
00:16:29.149 --> 00:16:31.401
I'll find you and pick you up.
Mr. President.

87
00:16:31.501 --> 00:16:34.087
- You'll find what...
- See you on the ground.

88
00:16:34.187 --> 00:16:36.512
No. Morris... Wait!

89
00:16:38.719 --> 00:16:39.763
Morris!

90
00:16:45.149 --> 00:16:47.417
- What about the crew?
- Our concern is the President.

91
00:16:47.517 --> 00:16:50.551
- Get out now!
- Go!

92
00:16:51.338 --> 00:16:54.371
Clay. jump. go!

93
00:16:59.146 --> 00:17:03.147
There's something wrong. sir.
I don't see any parachutes opening.

94
00:19:36.269 --> 00:19:38.038
The Air Force One mayday was verified.

95
00:19:38.138 --> 00:19:41.565
the evacuation protocol was clearly
triggered. and the POTUS escape pod

96
00:19:41.665 --> 00:19:43.577
- seems to have been jettisoned.
- Occupants?

97
00:19:43.777 --> 00:19:44.878
- One.
- I see.

98
00:19:44.978 --> 00:19:49.913
And then we lost everything. all coms.
radar profile. cell phone signals. gone.

99
00:19:52.086 --> 00:19:54.621
Mr. Vice President. I want
to introduce Fred Herbert.

100
00:19:54.721 --> 00:19:58.092
Fred is our longest serving field
operative the CIA has ever had.

101
00:19:58.492 --> 00:20:00.661
We finally convinced him
to come back to Langley.

102
00:20:00.761 --> 00:20:02.863
He now heads our terrorist intel unit.

103
00:20:02.963 --> 00:20:06.099
General. if you would start to fill
Fred in on our known knowns.

104
00:20:06.199 --> 00:20:08.335
Mr. Herbert. sir.

105
00:20:08.435 --> 00:20:12.506
Thirty-six minutes ago. we got an evac
distress signal from Air Force One.

106
00:20:12.606 --> 00:20:14.875
We lost coms immediately thereafter.

107
00:20:14.975 --> 00:20:18.478
At T minus 32. Air Force One

108
00:20:18.578 --> 00:20:21.982
and its entire fighter escort
fell off the grid.

109
00:20:22.082 --> 00:20:26.117
They were over Finland. en route
to Helsinki for a pre-G8 summit.

110
00:20:27.687 --> 00:20:29.339
Sir...

111
00:20:29.439 --> 00:20:32.509
We think this is the most serious
terrorist action since 9/11.

112
00:20:32.659 --> 00:20:34.878
Just a minute here. just to be clear.

113
00:20:34.978 --> 00:20:37.577
For all we know.
this was a mechanical failure.

114
00:20:37.677 --> 00:20:40.908
- On five planes. simultaneously?
- One explodes. takes out the others.

115
00:20:41.008 --> 00:20:44.121
- That's a stretch.
- Well. any explanation is a stretch.

116
00:20:44.271 --> 00:20:47.307
Right now. I'm saying we don't
want to rush to conclusions.

117
00:20:47.407 --> 00:20:51.044
It was a terrorist action.
employing a five to 10 man unit.

118
00:20:51.144 --> 00:20:55.282
They have money. They used Chinese-made.
shoulder-mounted surface-to-air missiles.

119
00:20:55.382 --> 00:20:58.684
- and they had a guy on the inside.
- Well. how the hell could you know that?

120
00:20:58.784 --> 00:21:02.189
They had money. they had to buy
the hardware. It was a five to 10 man unit.

121
00:21:02.289 --> 00:21:04.958
How do you think they transported
and simultaneously fired the SAMs?

122
00:21:05.058 --> 00:21:07.794
Shoulder-mounted SAMs
can't reach passenger jet altitude.

123
00:21:08.094 --> 00:21:09.963
They can.

124
00:21:10.063 --> 00:21:12.699
If the plane is on
its landing trajectory.

125
00:21:12.799 --> 00:21:14.768
and if the point of firing

126
00:21:14.868 --> 00:21:18.255
is at a higher than usual altitude.
like the side of a mountain...

127
00:21:18.355 --> 00:21:21.842
But Air Force One was fitted with
every countermeasure known to man.

128
00:21:21.942 --> 00:21:25.095
That's the job of the guy
on the inside. to disable them.

129
00:21:25.195 --> 00:21:27.898
Wait. he used a jammer. an EMP device?

130
00:21:27.998 --> 00:21:30.383
Or a screwdriver and a pair of pliers.

131
00:21:30.483 --> 00:21:33.053
What about getting a man
on Air Force One?

132
00:21:33.153 --> 00:21:35.422
How could they penetrate
security that tight?

133
00:21:35.522 --> 00:21:37.691
Same way they always do.

134
00:21:37.791 --> 00:21:41.060
Money. sex...

135
00:21:41.160 --> 00:21:43.096
or God.

136
00:21:43.196 --> 00:21:45.899
Any suggestions?

137
00:21:45.999 --> 00:21:48.869
There's only one thing left.
Find the President.

138
00:21:48.969 --> 00:21:51.402
kill the sons of bitches
who are after him...

139
00:21:52.405 --> 00:21:53.485
bring him home.

140
00:22:33.613 --> 00:22:37.981
This is Agent Echo-Mike.
calling all agents on the ground.

141
00:22:38.552 --> 00:22:41.176
Respond immediately.

142
00:22:42.021 --> 00:22:45.822
I repeat. Agent Echo-Mike.

143
00:22:46.292 --> 00:22:48.859
Is anyone receiving?

144
00:22:50.096 --> 00:22:54.331
No one. Glad to hear it. over and out.

145
00:23:01.374 --> 00:23:05.376
Angel is down. We're good to go.

146
00:25:01.395 --> 00:25:06.166
<i>Please stay inside. help is on the way.</i>

147
00:25:06.266 --> 00:25:11.234
<i>Do not exit the rescue pod
under any circumstance.</i>

148
00:25:12.472 --> 00:25:17.677
<i>Please stay inside.
help is on the way...</i>

149
00:25:23.917 --> 00:25:26.424
Show yourself!

150
00:25:35.294 --> 00:25:37.248
Come out!

151
00:25:45.538 --> 00:25:47.604
Please...

152
00:26:10.163 --> 00:26:12.532
What language is this?

153
00:26:12.632 --> 00:26:15.398
Can you show yourself. please?

154
00:26:17.103 --> 00:26:20.303
From what planet are you from?

155
00:26:21.908 --> 00:26:25.497
I am from Earth.
Is this some kid I'm talking to?

156
00:26:26.512 --> 00:26:30.513
- Do you come in peace?
- Yes.

157
00:26:31.284 --> 00:26:35.121
Yes. I... I come in peace.
Most definitely. yes. I...

158
00:26:35.221 --> 00:26:40.390
Wait. wait. don't hang...
"Don't hang up." What's wrong with me?

159
00:26:42.428 --> 00:26:46.563
Look. could you please just come out?

160
00:26:53.248 --> 00:26:58.411
Kid. hey!
Can we... lose the bow and arrow?

161
00:26:58.511 --> 00:27:00.077
Who are you?

162
00:27:01.347 --> 00:27:04.280
You don't recognize me?

163
00:27:05.952 --> 00:27:09.289
I'm William Allen Moore.

164
00:27:09.489 --> 00:27:11.921
the President...

165
00:27:12.158 --> 00:27:14.594
of the United States.

166
00:27:14.694 --> 00:27:16.426
Prove it.

167
00:27:26.139 --> 00:27:28.171
Stay.

168
00:27:52.632 --> 00:27:55.835
- Are you hurt?
- No.

169
00:27:56.335 --> 00:28:01.240
I am lost. And I could use your help.

170
00:28:01.340 --> 00:28:03.706
Do you have a phone?

171
00:28:04.543 --> 00:28:07.610
No. no. no. no. a real phone.

172
00:28:08.214 --> 00:28:12.882
Or is your house close by.
a town. small village?

173
00:28:14.353 --> 00:28:16.806
Where did you come from?
I mean. there must be something.

174
00:28:16.906 --> 00:28:20.239
I mean. did you just pop up
out of the ground?

175
00:28:22.028 --> 00:28:24.527
Vice President.

176
00:28:25.198 --> 00:28:28.465
we have located the rescue pod tracker.

177
00:28:31.137 --> 00:28:34.904
Sir. the situation is under control.

178
00:28:36.209 --> 00:28:37.811
<i>This is Genik 1 to Command.</i>

179
00:28:37.911 --> 00:28:40.346
<i>We have confirmed signal
from the President's escape pod.</i>

180
00:28:40.446 --> 00:28:42.913
<i>We are closing in on it now.</i>

181
00:28:43.749 --> 00:28:45.919
<i>ETA. one minute.</i>

182
00:28:46.019 --> 00:28:49.386
Copy that. Genik 1.
secure the President.

183
00:29:41.007 --> 00:29:43.910
<i>This is Genik 1. the pod is not here.</i>

184
00:29:44.010 --> 00:29:45.979
- What?
- Repeat that. Genik 1.

185
00:29:46.079 --> 00:29:48.448
We did not copy. over.

186
00:29:48.548 --> 00:29:51.050
<i>The homing beacon and the escape
pod must have separated. sir.</i>

187
00:29:51.150 --> 00:29:54.137
<i>I say again. the President is not here.</i>

188
00:29:54.237 --> 00:29:56.703
God in heaven!

189
00:29:57.440 --> 00:30:01.841
Genik 1. return to base.
await further instructions.

190
00:30:02.345 --> 00:30:06.479
- Over and out.
- <i>Roger that. Genik 1 out.</i>

191
00:30:08.751 --> 00:30:10.586
I apologize. sir.

192
00:30:10.886 --> 00:30:13.689
You're telling me we lost our President

193
00:30:13.789 --> 00:30:17.123
like you lose a set of car keys.

194
00:30:17.727 --> 00:30:22.098
This is the most powerful nation
in the history of the planet.

195
00:30:22.198 --> 00:30:24.764
Look at me!

196
00:30:25.034 --> 00:30:26.836
This is America.

197
00:30:26.936 --> 00:30:30.640
and as Vice President
of this great nation.

198
00:30:30.740 --> 00:30:36.342
I am commanding you
to sort this shit out!

199
00:30:47.256 --> 00:30:49.092
Interestingly. my department

200
00:30:49.192 --> 00:30:53.930
has registered precisely no chatter
about an action of this sort.

201
00:30:54.030 --> 00:30:57.100
Which leaves us
with the trickiest possibility.

202
00:30:57.600 --> 00:30:59.435
<i>The lone wolf. the jackal.</i>

203
00:30:59.535 --> 00:31:03.406
<i>who got his own agenda.
affiliated to no particular cause.</i>

204
00:31:03.506 --> 00:31:07.727
<i>Extremely hard to track.
impossible to predict.</i>

205
00:31:07.827 --> 00:31:11.280
And finally we have the central question...
What do they actually want?

206
00:31:11.380 --> 00:31:14.547
<i>What is the purpose of their...</i>

207
00:31:15.017 --> 00:31:16.485
<i>operation?</i>

208
00:31:16.585 --> 00:31:20.089
Well. that we do know.
Their intention was to assassinate

209
00:31:20.189 --> 00:31:22.284
- the President of the United States.
- I'm not sure.

210
00:31:22.384 --> 00:31:25.411
What. there might be another intention
behind blowing up his plane?

211
00:31:26.021 --> 00:31:29.394
Big game hunting never got any bigger.

212
00:31:32.268 --> 00:31:36.506
Based on our knowledge at this moment
in time. the President is not assassinated.

213
00:31:36.606 --> 00:31:39.976
We do know that the evac was triggered.
Maybe that's what they wanted.

214
00:31:40.076 --> 00:31:41.711
<i>To capture him. to take him alive.</i>

215
00:31:41.811 --> 00:31:46.378
God damn it. so they can show off
their trophy and make demands.

216
00:31:48.918 --> 00:31:51.893
- Kazim.
- Ready.

217
00:31:58.895 --> 00:32:01.994
- Where is he?
<i>- Help is on the way...</i>

218
00:32:03.432 --> 00:32:04.834
You're lucky.

219
00:32:04.934 --> 00:32:08.137
Gotta be honest with you. young man.
I'm not feeling so lucky right now.

220
00:32:08.237 --> 00:32:14.741
But you are. If I hadn't found you.
you'd have zero chance of survival.

221
00:32:16.879 --> 00:32:20.449
I'm a hunter. This is my home.

222
00:32:20.549 --> 00:32:24.587
With this. I can catch us food.
and keep us safe.

223
00:32:24.687 --> 00:32:27.456
- Safe from what?
- Bears.

224
00:32:27.556 --> 00:32:30.760
- There's bears out here?
- Yeah.

225
00:32:30.860 --> 00:32:33.129
And you could kill one with that thing?

226
00:32:33.229 --> 00:32:34.864
Yeah.

227
00:32:34.964 --> 00:32:37.563
Have you done it before?

228
00:32:38.267 --> 00:32:40.219
- Yes.
- Really?

229
00:32:40.319 --> 00:32:46.038
No. but my dad has.
And I could do it too.

230
00:32:46.775 --> 00:32:48.478
All right.

231
00:32:48.578 --> 00:32:50.613
Your dad sounds like a great man.

232
00:32:51.013 --> 00:32:53.749
The best hunter there is.

233
00:32:53.849 --> 00:32:55.551
Like me.

234
00:32:55.651 --> 00:32:57.650
Right.

235
00:32:59.522 --> 00:33:02.458
- And your father's name is?
- Tapio.

236
00:33:02.758 --> 00:33:05.128
Tapio. And you are?

237
00:33:05.228 --> 00:33:07.897
- Oskari.
- Oskari.

238
00:33:07.997 --> 00:33:11.765
Well. like I said before. my name's
William. but you can call me Bill.

239
00:33:13.769 --> 00:33:17.437
Nah. I call you President.
sounds better.

240
00:33:17.790 --> 00:33:21.924
And you. you can call me Ranger.

241
00:33:25.380 --> 00:33:27.347
Right.

242
00:33:28.117 --> 00:33:29.877
Here.

