- What did he say?
- We've got a stowaway.

501
00:57:24.936 --> 00:57:26.582
It's that damn kid!

502
00:57:27.288 --> 00:57:29.955
Shake him off.
Return him back to his forest.

503
00:57:32.048 --> 00:57:33.959
Ranger. Ranger. look out!

504
00:57:38.332 --> 00:57:41.365
Hang on. they're trying
to knock you off.

505
00:57:43.605 --> 00:57:46.737
Knock him off.
Use it like a wrecking ball.

506
00:57:50.378 --> 00:57:54.248
- Ranger. you shouldn't be here.
- Don't worry. Mr. President.

507
00:57:54.348 --> 00:57:56.415
- I will save you.
- Hang on!

508
00:57:57.318 --> 00:58:00.785
Ranger! Ranger! Ranger!

509
00:58:02.089 --> 00:58:04.092
Are you all right?

510
00:58:04.992 --> 00:58:07.012
Get off!

511
00:58:07.395 --> 00:58:09.964
- You have to jump!
- Oh. hell. no!

512
00:58:10.064 --> 00:58:12.340
Now. shoot the boy. shoot him!
Shoot him!

513
00:58:29.683 --> 00:58:32.020
No! No!

514
00:58:32.120 --> 00:58:35.353
I got you! Come on! Grab the strap!

515
00:58:37.491 --> 00:58:40.895
- I'll cut you loose.
- No. no. no. that's not a good idea.

516
00:58:40.995 --> 00:58:45.130
- Close the lid.
- This is not a good idea!

517
00:58:51.705 --> 00:58:53.404
No!

518
00:58:53.507 --> 00:58:56.925
Hazar. get me on the ground. now!

519
00:59:09.256 --> 00:59:11.854
President. you okay?

520
00:59:11.954 --> 00:59:14.462
How the hell did I survive that?

521
00:59:14.562 --> 00:59:16.831
And where are my soldiers?

522
00:59:16.931 --> 00:59:20.668
I'm the commander of the biggest. bad-ass.
ass-kicking armed forces on the planet.

523
00:59:20.768 --> 00:59:23.637
Why aren't they scouring
this wilderness trying to rescue me?

524
00:59:23.737 --> 00:59:25.606
There's no one to help us.

525
00:59:25.706 --> 00:59:28.743
Not my dad. and not your army.

526
00:59:28.843 --> 00:59:31.512
We have to help ourselves.

527
00:59:31.612 --> 00:59:34.074
Instead of looking tough.

528
00:59:34.982 --> 00:59:37.051
we have to be tough.

529
00:59:37.151 --> 00:59:38.686
Right.

530
00:59:39.086 --> 00:59:40.836
Okay.

531
00:59:40.936 --> 00:59:42.620
Oskari. look out!

532
00:59:52.099 --> 00:59:54.238
This your idea of being tough?

533
00:59:54.538 --> 00:59:57.421
No. This is.

534
00:59:57.521 --> 00:59:59.754
No. Oskari. no. No!

535
01:00:10.818 --> 01:00:13.447
What the hell are they doing?

536
01:00:27.501 --> 01:00:30.035
We're gonna die!

537
01:01:31.365 --> 01:01:33.701
You think we lost 'em?

538
01:01:33.801 --> 01:01:35.667
I hope so.

539
01:01:47.581 --> 01:01:49.160
Look.

540
01:02:01.462 --> 01:02:03.598
Is that what I think it is?

541
01:02:04.298 --> 01:02:08.336
Affirmative. We just found
the crash site of Air Force One.

542
01:02:08.436 --> 01:02:10.637
Give those GPS coordinates to the SEALs.

543
01:02:10.737 --> 01:02:12.787
Yes. sir.

544
01:02:36.430 --> 01:02:38.464
Shit.

545
01:02:41.502 --> 01:02:43.223
My dad is waiting for me.

546
01:02:44.805 --> 01:02:47.516
We've got only one hour.

547
01:02:47.841 --> 01:02:49.874
Can you swim?

548
01:02:50.211 --> 01:02:52.480
Of course I can.

549
01:02:52.580 --> 01:02:54.545
They're back.

550
01:02:56.183 --> 01:02:59.584
- We have to get in that plane.
- Let's go.

551
01:03:23.110 --> 01:03:24.976
Switch to thermal imaging.

552
01:03:29.016 --> 01:03:30.587
They're going in.

553
01:03:34.401 --> 01:03:37.358
Great. Stick with me.

554
01:03:37.458 --> 01:03:39.557
Oh. Jesus.

555
01:03:40.628 --> 01:03:44.896
Looks like the upper deck may be clean.
Come on. swim with me.

556
01:04:23.971 --> 01:04:25.870
Okay.

557
01:04:26.607 --> 01:04:29.198
We're gonna be okay now.

558
01:04:29.777 --> 01:04:32.913
All we have to do is...
wait for the army.

559
01:04:33.013 --> 01:04:34.281
But...

560
01:04:34.381 --> 01:04:36.467
Don't worry.

561
01:04:39.052 --> 01:04:41.485
I'll get you to your father.

562
01:05:04.878 --> 01:05:06.847
What is that?

563
01:05:06.947 --> 01:05:10.581
Well. if it's not the cavalry.
it can't be good.

564
01:05:25.165 --> 01:05:26.793
Do you think they're gone?

565
01:05:43.667 --> 01:05:46.407
What have we here?

566
01:05:55.696 --> 01:05:56.897
Oskari! Oskari!

567
01:05:56.997 --> 01:06:00.100
Mr. President.
please accept my apologies.

568
01:06:00.200 --> 01:06:03.504
My mission was to take you alive.
but now I have no choice but to kill you.

569
01:06:03.604 --> 01:06:06.874
- Your mission?
- You were going to be held captive.

570
01:06:06.974 --> 01:06:10.911
filmed. documenting every moment
of your imprisonment.

571
01:06:11.111 --> 01:06:13.380
and after seven days
you would be martyred.

572
01:06:13.680 --> 01:06:16.427
The images would horrify the world.
and the world would know

573
01:06:16.527 --> 01:06:20.814
- the war on terror is not over.
- What the hell kind of terrorist are you?

574
01:06:20.914 --> 01:06:23.300
If it's any consolation to you
before you die. Mr. President.

575
01:06:23.400 --> 01:06:25.486
I'm actually on your side.

576
01:06:26.560 --> 01:06:28.212
And what does that mean?

577
01:06:28.312 --> 01:06:30.330
That's a long story.

578
01:06:30.430 --> 01:06:33.817
Some other time. I'm done here.

579
01:06:33.917 --> 01:06:35.280
Yes. you are.

580
01:06:44.177 --> 01:06:47.244
Well. I know how that feels.

581
01:07:01.462 --> 01:07:02.996
Oh. God!

582
01:07:45.481 --> 01:07:47.155
What's that?

583
01:07:48.575 --> 01:07:51.341
That was a deer.

584
01:07:52.245 --> 01:07:54.444
You little brat.

585
01:08:04.157 --> 01:08:06.424
You gotta cock it. mother...

586
01:08:22.843 --> 01:08:25.309
We have to get out of here.

587
01:08:28.048 --> 01:08:30.566
We can swim out.

588
01:08:34.321 --> 01:08:36.089
I don't think so.

589
01:08:36.189 --> 01:08:39.120
There is one other thing
we can try. Come on.

590
01:08:40.961 --> 01:08:42.963
She's gonna blow! Go now!

591
01:08:43.263 --> 01:08:45.212
Not without Hazar.

592
01:08:47.401 --> 01:08:51.200
- I said. go now!
- Not without Hazar!

593
01:08:56.743 --> 01:08:59.246
Don't worry. President.

594
01:08:59.346 --> 01:09:00.914
I got this.

595
01:09:01.714 --> 01:09:03.820
Here we go.

596
01:09:25.038 --> 01:09:27.771
Do you read me now?

597
01:11:23.924 --> 01:11:28.962
Get out! Get out of the truck!
Move! I said. move! Get out!

598
01:11:29.062 --> 01:11:33.266
All right. clear the area! Let's go!
Come on. move! Go. go. go!

599
01:11:33.366 --> 01:11:36.270
Move straight ahead! Move!
Do not look at me.

600
01:11:36.770 --> 01:11:39.222
Weapons! All weapons to the ground now!

601
01:11:39.322 --> 01:11:41.479
- Hands behind your back.
- All right. this way. Move!

602
01:11:41.579 --> 01:11:44.661
Get down! Get down on your knees!
Nobody move!

603
01:11:44.761 --> 01:11:46.897
SEAL team to base. we're on the ground.

604
01:11:46.997 --> 01:11:49.850
Looks like the entire lake's
been vaporized.

605
01:11:49.950 --> 01:11:51.551
Copy that.

606
01:11:51.651 --> 01:11:54.318
There is no way
they could've survived that.

607
01:11:55.589 --> 01:11:58.188
Mr. Vice President. sir.

608
01:11:58.625 --> 01:12:01.926
I'm sorry. but you have to be
formally sworn in.

609
01:12:03.497 --> 01:12:06.764
Take the office of President
of the United States.

610
01:12:10.337 --> 01:12:13.306
For my God and country.

611
01:12:14.107 --> 01:12:15.776
I accept.

612
01:12:16.176 --> 01:12:18.379
Hurry up! Move in. over there!

613
01:12:18.479 --> 01:12:21.415
Copy that. We're not coming home
until we find the President's body.

614
01:12:21.915 --> 01:12:23.680
<i>Or what's left of him anyway.</i>

615
01:12:31.091 --> 01:12:32.476
What the hell?

616
01:12:32.576 --> 01:12:35.142
Sir. above. incoming.

617
01:12:36.529 --> 01:12:39.800
Base. we have an unidentified
flying object closing fast.

618
01:12:39.900 --> 01:12:43.667
<i>you should have a visual on this.
Streaming now. take a look.</i>

619
01:12:52.813 --> 01:12:55.982
Stay alert. The object is on the ground.

620
01:12:56.082 --> 01:12:59.083
I say again.
the object is on the ground.

621
01:12:59.919 --> 01:13:01.652
Stay alert.

622
01:13:02.222 --> 01:13:04.848
And I see movement.

623
01:13:06.326 --> 01:13:09.162
I've got a young boy...

624
01:13:09.262 --> 01:13:10.791
with a bow and arrow.

625
01:13:27.773 --> 01:13:28.906
Stay where you are.

626
01:14:00.313 --> 01:14:02.482
You must be Tapio.

627
01:14:02.582 --> 01:14:04.785
- Yes.
- I've heard a great deal about you.

628
01:14:05.285 --> 01:14:08.054
I understand you're a great hunter.

629
01:14:08.154 --> 01:14:11.155
Just so you know. so is he.

630
01:14:13.460 --> 01:14:16.263
You have an amazing son.

631
01:14:16.363 --> 01:14:18.316
Bravest man I've ever met.

632
01:14:41.184 --> 01:14:44.824
Good to see you. Mr. President.
Are you all right?

633
01:14:44.924 --> 01:14:46.326
Well...

634
01:14:46.426 --> 01:14:49.463
considering I've been
betrayed today. hunted.

635
01:14:49.963 --> 01:14:53.366
locked in a freezer.
ejected from the same plane twice.

636
01:14:53.666 --> 01:14:57.756
yeah. I'm... I'm doing quite well.
Thanks to this young man here.

637
01:15:02.075 --> 01:15:05.111
I'm proud to serve
under your command. Mr. President.

638
01:15:05.711 --> 01:15:07.117
SEAL team one reporting.

639
01:15:07.217 --> 01:15:09.516
<i>I've got eyes on the President
and he is secure.</i>

640
01:15:09.616 --> 01:15:11.973
<i>I repeat. the President is secure.</i>

641
01:15:29.469 --> 01:15:32.673
Well. that was quite a screw-up.

642
01:15:32.773 --> 01:15:35.842
Fifteen years I knew Hazar.

643
01:15:35.942 --> 01:15:40.577
Best and most loyal agent I ever had.
and what did we achieve?

644
01:15:41.147 --> 01:15:44.648
Instead of turning
the President into a martyr.

645
01:15:45.151 --> 01:15:47.684
we turn him into a hero.

646
01:15:49.856 --> 01:15:54.091
Not to mention. I lost my shot
at the Presidency.

647
01:15:56.363 --> 01:15:59.997
I've got one question for you. friend.
one question only.

648
01:16:00.467 --> 01:16:02.102
Can it get back to us?

649
01:16:02.502 --> 01:16:04.671
Can it get back to us?

650
01:16:04.771 --> 01:16:06.873
Well. Vice President.

651
01:16:06.973 --> 01:16:08.975
Morris is dead.

652
01:16:09.075 --> 01:16:11.608
Hazar is dead.

653
01:16:12.078 --> 01:16:14.259
all his men are dead.

654
01:16:22.622 --> 01:16:25.155
And you're dead.

655
01:16:26.259 --> 01:16:28.292
So...

656
01:16:29.662 --> 01:16:31.729
in answer to your question.

657
01:16:33.700 --> 01:16:36.633
getting back to anyone?

658
01:16:38.137 --> 01:16:41.404
I would say. no.

659
01:16:43.877 --> 01:16:47.259
It's not getting back to anyone.

659
01:16:48.305 --> 01:17:48.707
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-
